student_first_dialogue: Hi, I'm feeling really guilty about not being able to get my assignments done on time. I keep putting them off and I don't know why. It's like I'm stuck in this cycle of procrastination and I don't know how to get out of it.
Hey, I've been struggling to sleep lately. I've been lying awake for hours every night, and even when I do fall asleep, I wake up feeling exhausted. I just can't seem to catch up on rest.

Hi, I've been feeling really overwhelmed lately. I'm 20 years old and I feel like I should be financially independent by now, but I'm still relying on my parents for everything. I just can't stop thinking about it and it's affecting my mood and motivation.

Honestly, I just can't seem to motivate myself to log in to my online classes. It feels like such a chore, and I'm just going through the motions. I'm starting to think I'm just not cut out for this whole online learning thing.
Hi, I don't know why I'm here. I feel so ashamed about needing help. I should be able to handle my problems on my own.
Hey, I don't know why, but I just can't seem to find the energy to train anymore. I used to love it, but now it just feels like a chore. I'm so apathetic about it.
I'm really stressed out about our group project. We're supposed to present in front of the whole class, and I'm terrified I'll mess up and let everyone down. I feel so guilty just thinking about it.
Hi, I'm feeling really isolated lately. I had a big fight with my closest friends and now it feels like they're all avoiding me. I don't know what to do or how to fix it.

Hi, I'm really struggling with my grades lately. I just got my midterm results and I'm not doing well at all. I'm starting to feel like I'm not cut out for college. I'm doubting my abilities and it's affecting my motivation to even study.
I'm just really struggling in my classes, but I'm too ashamed to ask for help. I feel like I'm the only one who doesn't get it.

I just can't believe I got rejected from another internship. I feel like I'm not good enough. I've applied to so many places, and no one wants me. I'm starting to regret not taking that one offer I got last semester.
Hi, I'm really stressed out about my student loans. I feel like I'm drowning in debt and I don't know how I'm going to pay it off. It's always on my mind and it's affecting my focus on my studies.

I'm so frustrated with my friends right now. We've been friends since freshman year, but lately, it feels like they're not even making an effort to hang out or talk to me. I feel like I'm always the one initiating conversations and plans, and they just don't seem to care. I'm starting to resent them for it.

I'm really struggling with this feeling of self-doubt. I'm a team leader for a group project, and I'm worried that I won't be able to deliver what my team needs. I've been having these constant thoughts of "what if I fail?" and "what if I let everyone down?"
I'm so anxious about the upcoming competitions. I feel like I need to win, or else I'll let everyone down. My parents, my coach, even myself. I just can't shake off this feeling of pressure.

I feel like my whole world has been turned upside down. My boyfriend and I broke up last week, and I'm still trying to process everything. We were together for three years, and I thought we were happy. I don't know how to move on from this. I just feel so lost and heartbroken.

Hi, I'm so glad I came in today. I've been feeling really overwhelmed and stressed out lately. I just can't seem to stop thinking about everything. Every little thing becomes a huge deal in my head, and it's exhausting.

I'm so frustrated, I've been having trouble sleeping for weeks now. I've tried everything: going to bed earlier, avoiding caffeine, exercising regularly... nothing seems to work. I'm exhausted all the time and it's affecting my mood and grades.

I don't know, I just can't seem to sleep at night. I'll lie awake for hours, thinking about nothing and everything at the same time. It's like my brain just won't shut off. And when I do finally fall asleep, I wake up feeling like I've been hit by a truck. I'm so tired all the time, and it's affecting my grades, my social life... everything.

Hi, I'm just really frustrated and feeling so down on myself. I've applied to what feels like a million internships and jobs, and I keep getting rejected. I'm starting to think I'm just not good enough.

Hi, I'm really struggling with social anxiety. I feel like I'm constantly overthinking every interaction, every conversation, every little thing. It's exhausting. I just feel like I'm not good enough, like I'm always on the verge of saying or doing something stupid.

I just feel so lonely all the time. My boyfriend and I have been in a long-distance relationship for a year now, and it's just getting harder and harder. We barely get to see each other, and when we do, it's always so rushed. I feel like I'm just stuck in this limbo, and I don't know how to make it work.
Hi, I'm really nervous about talking to you about this, but I just feel so anxious in social situations. I avoid parties and gatherings because I'm afraid of saying something stupid or being judged.

Honestly, I just don't feel like training anymore. I've been doing it for months, and I'm not seeing any progress. It's like I'm just going through the motions. I feel so apathetic about the whole thing.
I'm really struggling with managing my money. I always seem to overspend and then I feel so guilty about it. I don't know how to stop.

Hi, I'm feeling so much pressure to win competitions. I'm a debater and my team is counting on me, but I'm getting really anxious about not meeting their expectations. I keep thinking "what if I mess up?" and it's affecting my performance.
I don't know why I'm even here. I feel so ashamed. I've been struggling with my coursework and I'm afraid to ask for help. I feel like I should be able to do it on my own.
I'm just so done with my friends. We always seem to be at odds with each other and it's exhausting. I feel like they never listen to me or care about my feelings.
Honestly, I'm just so done with online learning. It's like, I'm stuck in front of a screen all day, and I just can't seem to focus. I feel like I'm falling behind, and it's just really frustrating.
Hi, I'm really struggling with public speaking. Just the thought of it makes me incredibly anxious. I avoid it at all costs, but I know I need to overcome this fear.

Hi, I'm just really feeling hopeless right now. I was supposed to be the star player on my team, and now I'm sidelined with an injury. I feel like my whole identity is wrapped up in sports, and without it, I'm nothing.
Hi, I'm really nervous about speaking up in class. I always feel like everyone is judging me, and I'm scared of saying something stupid. I just want to hide and avoid participating altogether.

Hey, I'm really struggling to balance my sports commitments with my schoolwork. I feel like I'm constantly running from one thing to another and I'm not doing well in either area. I'm really stressed out about it.

I just feel so overwhelmed all the time. My parents are always on my case about getting good grades, going to a top college, and getting a high-paying job. They never seem to be satisfied with what I do, no matter how hard I try. I feel like I'm walking on eggshells around them, always worried about disappointing them.

I just feel so overwhelmed all the time. My parents are always on my case about something. They want me to get straight A's, play sports, volunteer, and have a part-time job. I'm just so tired of trying to please them. I feel like I'm never good enough.

Hi, I'm feeling really worried about my financial situation. I'm 20 and still dependent on my parents for everything. I want to be financially independent, but I have no idea how to make that happen. I feel like I'm stuck.
Hi, I'm really struggling with managing my money. I feel so guilty about it. I keep overspending and I'm worried I'm going to end up in debt. I don't know how to stop it.
I'm so frustrated with my friends right now. We're always fighting about something, and it feels like they never listen to me or care about my feelings. I'm just so resentful towards them.
Hi, I'm just really struggling with online learning. I feel like I'm not learning anything and it's so hard to stay motivated. I'm constantly stressed about keeping up.

I'm so frustrated with my friends right now. We always seem to disagree on everything, and it feels like they're never listening to me. I feel like I'm always walking on eggshells around them, trying not to say something that will start a fight. I'm just so resentful of the whole situation.
Hi, I feel really stuck. I've been putting off this project for weeks, and now it's due soon. I just feel like I'm not good enough, and I'm going to fail.

Hi, I'm just really struggling with taking risks. I feel like I'm always holding back and playing it safe, but it's holding me back from achieving my goals. I just can't seem to shake off this fear of failure.
Hi, I'm just really struggling with my long-distance relationship. I feel so uncertain about everything. Is it even worth it?

I feel so guilty about not being able to motivate myself to study for my upcoming exams. I know I should be preparing, but I just can't seem to get myself to do it. I've been putting it off for weeks now, and it's getting closer and closer.

Hi, I'm really struggling with managing my money. I feel like I'm drowning in debt and I have no idea how to get out of it. I'm constantly worried about not being able to pay my bills on time. (Overwhelm)

I just can't seem to get anything done. I know I have deadlines, but I just keep putting things off until the last minute. It's so frustrating because I know I'm capable of doing better, but I just can't seem to get motivated.

I'm just so exhausted all the time. I feel like I'm constantly juggling school and my part-time job, and I'm not doing well in either one. I'm barely sleeping, and when I do, I'm plagued by anxiety about all the things I need to do. I just feel like I'm stuck in this never-ending cycle.

I just feel so devastated. My boyfriend and I broke up last week, and it's been really tough for me to focus on classes and stuff. I thought we were solid, but I guess I was wrong. I just can't stop thinking about him and what could've been.
I just feel so hopeless, Doc. I was supposed to be the star player on the team, and now I'm stuck on the sidelines with an injury. I don't know how I'm going to get back to where I was.

Hi, I'm really struggling with this team project. I'm worried that I'm going to let everyone down. We're relying on me to finish this part, and I just don't know if I can do it. I feel like I'm not good enough.
I feel like I'm always left out of social events at school. Nobody invites me to parties or hangs out with me during lunch. It makes me so sad and unwanted.

Hi, I'm just really anxious about my career choices. I feel like I'm expected to have it all figured out, but I have no idea what I want to do. I'm worried that I'll make the wrong choice and regret it.

Hi, I'm feeling really overwhelmed. I'm on the school soccer team and I love it, but it's taking up so much of my time. I'm struggling to keep up with my schoolwork and I'm worried I'm going to fall behind. I don't want to give up soccer, but I don't know how to balance everything.

Hi, I'm really struggling with self-discipline. I always seem to put off my assignments until the last minute, and it's affecting my grades. I feel so guilty about it because I know I'm capable of doing better.

Hi, I'm feeling really down lately. I feel like I'm always being left out of social events and activities with my friends. It hurts to see them having fun without me on social media. I just wish I could be a part of their group.

Hi, I'm just feeling really lost and alone right now. I don't know what I want to do with my life, and it seems like everyone around me has their life figured out. I feel like I'm just drifting through each day without any purpose.
Hi, I'm just feeling really left out lately. Everyone seems to have their cliques and friend groups, and I'm just kind of... floating around. I feel like I don't fit in anywhere.

Hi counselor, I'm really struggling with the desire to be financially independent. I feel like I'm stuck in a rut and can't seem to get ahead. I'm constantly worrying about my future and it's affecting my present. I just can't stop overthinking about it
Hi, I'm really worried about not getting a good job after graduation. I feel like I've worked so hard, but what if it's all for nothing?

Hi, I'm feeling really down about myself. I've applied to over 10 internships and job openings, and I haven't gotten even a single callback or interview. I'm starting to think I'm just not good enough.
Hi, I'm just feeling really overwhelmed about my student loans. I'm not sure how I'm going to pay them off, and it's stressing me out so much. I feel like I'm drowning in debt.

Hi, I'm really struggling with financial stress. I'm constantly worried about making ends meet, and it's affecting my performance in class. I feel like I'm drowning in debt and I don't know how to get out of it.

Hi, I'm really frustrated with myself. I just can't seem to get anything done on time. I procrastinate, I put things off, and then I'm left feeling overwhelmed and stressed out. I wish I could just be more disciplined and get things done.
I just can't shake off this feeling of guilt. I'm part of a group project, and I'm struggling to keep up with the others. I'm afraid of letting them down, and it's eating away at me.
Hi, I'm really stressed about my upcoming exams. I feel like I'm not prepared at all and I'm worried that I'm going to fail. I've been having trouble sleeping and I just feel so anxious all the time.

I'm just so frustrated with my financial situation. I'm struggling to make ends meet and it's affecting my studies. I don't know how I'm going to pay my tuition fees. I feel like I'm drowning in debt.
Hey, I'm really struggling to set goals for myself. I feel like I'm constantly overthinking and second-guessing everything. I just can't seem to make a decision.

Hi, I'm just feeling really frustrated with my financial situation. I'm working part-time, but it's not enough to cover all my expenses. I feel like I'll never be able to pay off my student loans. It's just so overwhelming.
I'm so guilty about not being able to finish my assignments on time. I always put things off until the last minute, and it's like I'm stuck in this never-ending cycle of procrastination.
Hi, I'm really disappointed in myself. I was supposed to be the star player on my team, and now I'm out for the season with an injury. I feel like I've let everyone down.
Hi, I'm really nervous about an upcoming presentation in my class. I'm afraid I'll stumble over my words or forget what to say. Just thinking about it makes my heart race.

I just got my exam results and I'm really disappointed in myself. I've been getting low grades all semester and I feel like a total failure. I'm ashamed to even talk about it. (looks down, avoiding eye contact)
I don't know why I'm here. I don't need help. I can handle my problems on my own.
I'm really struggling with this project. I'm part of a team, and I'm worried that I'm going to mess up and let everyone down. I just feel so inadequate and unsure of myself.
I just feel so lost and unsure of who I am or what I want to do with my life. I'm stuck in this limbo and it's really frustrating.

I'm really struggling with managing my money. I feel like I'm constantly worried about not having enough, and it's affecting my focus on school. I just don't know where to start or how to make it work.

I'm really struggling with managing my money. I feel like I'm constantly worried about not having enough, and it's affecting my focus on school. I just don't know where to start or how to make it work.
Hi, I'm really worried about my financial situation. I'm struggling to pay my tuition fees and living expenses. I feel like I'm drowning in debt.
I feel so stuck. I'm always afraid to take risks and try new things. I'm worried that I'll fail or make a fool of myself. What if I'm not good enough?

Hi, counselor. I'm really worried about everything lately. I overthink every little thing, and it's driving me crazy. I feel like I'm constantly on edge, waiting for the other shoe to drop. I just can't seem to shake this feeling of dread.

Hi, I'm really struggling with my grades right now. I'm just not doing well in any of my classes and it's making me feel like I'm not cut out for college. I'm starting to wonder if I'm even smart enough to be here.
Hi, I'm really struggling with taking risks. I overthink everything and it's holding me back from pursuing opportunities that could be great for me. I feel like I'm stuck in a rut.
Honestly, I just can't seem to care about my online classes. I mean, I'm just going through the motions, but I don't feel like I'm learning anything. It's all just so boring and disconnected.
I just got rejected from another internship. I'm so disappointed in myself. I feel like I'm not good enough.
Hi, I just don't feel like I fit in with my peer group. Everyone seems to have their own cliques and friend circles, and I'm just on the outside looking in. It makes me feel so insecure and unwanted.

Hi, I've been feeling really overwhelmed lately. I just want to be financially independent, but every time I think about it, I get caught up in all the what-ifs and maybes. I feel like I'm stuck in this endless cycle of overthinking.
I just feel like I'm not skilled enough in my major. Everyone around me seems to know so much more than I do. I'm constantly comparing myself to them and feeling inadequate.

I just feel like I'm always on the outside looking in. I'm afraid to talk to people, participate in class, or even hang out with friends because I'm terrified of saying something stupid or being judged. It's like I'm stuck in this bubble of loneliness and I don't know how to break free.

I'm just so exhausted, physically and mentally. I feel like I've been studying non-stop for weeks, and I'm starting to lose motivation. I'm not retaining anything, and I'm constantly worried about not meeting my grades. I just feel like I'm drowning in schoolwork.

I'm so frustrated with myself. I always set goals and make plans, but I never seem to follow through. I lack self-discipline, and it's holding me back in every aspect of my life. I feel like I'm stuck in this vicious cycle, and I don't know how to break free.
Hey, I'm just feeling really unmotivated to train for my sport lately. I used to love it, but now it just feels like a chore. I don't know why I'm even bothering.

Hi, I'm just feeling really frustrated about my financial situation. I have a bunch of debt from student loans and I'm struggling to make ends meet. I feel like I'm never going to be able to pay it off.

Hi, I'm really struggling with taking risks. I feel like I'm stuck in a rut and I'm not living up to my potential because I'm too scared to try new things. I spend hours overthinking every possible outcome, and it's exhausting. I just wish I could be more spontaneous and confident like my friends.

Hi, counselor. I'm really struggling with overthinking everything. I feel like I'm constantly second-guessing myself and it's really affecting my confidence. I just feel so uncertain about everything.
Hi, I'm really struggling with public speaking. I get nervous, my voice shakes, and I just freeze up. I'm worried that I'll never be able to get over this fear.

I'm so stuck. I just can't seem to set any goals for myself. I know I need to, but every time I try, I get caught up in thinking about all the what-ifs and maybes, and before I know it, hours have passed and I've gotten nowhere.
Hi, I'm really struggling with managing my money. I feel so guilty about all the mistakes I've made and the debt I've accumulated. I just feel like I'm not good at adulting.

I'm just so frustrated and regretful about all these rejections I've been getting. I've applied to like 10 internships and jobs, and not a single one has worked out. It feels like I'm not good enough.

Hi, I'm really struggling with this feeling that I don't belong here. I feel like I'm just pretending to be a smart student, and everyone's going to find out that I'm fake. I'm so scared that I'm not good enough.
Hi, I'm really nervous about an upcoming presentation in my class. I'm afraid of speaking in front of everyone and I'm worried that I'll mess up.

I'm just really overwhelmed with exams coming up. I feel like I'm not prepared at all, and I'm afraid I'm going to fail. I've been staying up late studying, but I still don't feel like I'm getting anything. I just feel so stuck.
Hi, I'm just really struggling with feeling like I'm not good enough. No matter how hard I try, I always feel like I'm failing. I'm just so insecure about everything.

Hey, I'm feeling really pressured lately. I'm 20 and still living with my parents. I want to be financially independent, but I don't know how to make it happen. I feel like I'm stuck and I'm not doing enough.

I'm so frustrated with myself. I always know what I need to do, but I just can't seem to get started. I put things off until the last minute, and then I'm up all night stressing out. I feel like I'm stuck in this cycle and I don't know how to get out.

Hi counselor, I'm feeling really anxious about my financial situation. I'm 20 and still dependent on my parents. I want to be financially independent, but every time I think about it, I start overthinking and feeling overwhelmed. I don't know where to start or how to make it happen.

Hi, counselor. I'm just feeling really discouraged about my training lately. I used to be so motivated and excited to improve, but now I just feel like I'm going through the motions. I don't know why I'm even bothering.
I don't know, it feels like my friends are all against me. We used to be so close, but now it feels like they're all ganging up on me. I just want to avoid them altogether.

Hi, I'm really struggling with this feeling that I don't belong here. I look around and see all these talented people, and I just feel like I'm pretending to be something I'm not. I'm so afraid that someone is going to figure out that I'm not as smart as they think I am.

Hi, I'm really nervous about an upcoming presentation in class. I'm afraid of speaking in front of everyone and I just can't seem to shake off this feeling. Even thinking about it now is making me anxious.

Hi, I'm really struggling in my classes. I just can't seem to understand the material no matter how hard I try. I feel like I'm the only one who doesn't get it. It's making me doubt myself and my abilities.
Hi, I'm really struggling with exam stress right now. I feel like I'm under so much pressure to perform well, and it's affecting my sleep, my appetite, everything. I just can't seem to shake it off.

Hi, I've been struggling with procrastination lately. I always put off my assignments until the last minute, and it's been causing me a lot of stress. I feel so guilty about it, like I'm not living up to my potential.
I just feel so stupid sometimes. I'm not good at anything, and I always make mistakes. I just wish I could be more confident like my friends.

Hi, I'm feeling really anxious about the upcoming competitions. I feel like I have to win or else I'll let everyone down. My parents, my coaches, even my teammates are all counting on me. It's like, I'm the only one who can bring home the trophy.

Honestly, I'm really stressed about my future. I'm not sure if I'll be able to get a good job after I graduate. I feel like everyone around me seems to have their lives figured out, and I'm just stuck.
Hi, I'm really stressed out about my student loans. I feel like I'm drowning in debt and I don't know how I'm going to pay them off. It's affecting my sleep, my relationships, everything.

Hi, I'm really struggling with online learning. I feel so isolated all the time. I'm stuck at home, staring at a screen, and it feels like I'm missing out on so much. I'm just not motivated to do anything.

Hey, I'm just feeling so exhausted all the time. I'm trying to balance school, work, and a social life, but it feels like I'm constantly running on empty. I'm always tired, and I just can't seem to catch up.
Hi, I just feel so guilty all the time. My parents are always on my case about my grades, my major, my career path... everything. I feel like I'm never good enough for them.

Hi, I'm feeling really overwhelmed and anxious about my studies. I just can't shake off the feeling that I don't belong here, that I'm just pretending to be something I'm not. Everyone else seems so confident and capable, while I'm struggling to keep up.
Hi, I'm so sorry to be here. I feel like I'm weak for needing help. I've been struggling in my classes and I just can't seem to get my grades up no matter how hard I try. I feel like I'm a failure.
I'm so frustrated with my friends right now. They always do things without considering my feelings, and it feels like they don't care about me at all. I'm getting really resentful towards them.

Hi, I'm really struggling to understand my subjects, especially math and science. I feel like I'm just not getting it, and it's making me feel so confused and frustrated.

Honestly, I'm really frustrated with myself. I just can't seem to stick to my goals or habits. I set out to do something, and a few days later, I'm right back to my old ways. I feel like I have no self-discipline whatsoever.

Hi, I'm just so frustrated. I haven't been sleeping well for weeks, and it's affecting my grades, my mood, everything. I feel like I've tried everything, but nothing seems to be working.

Hi, I'm really struggling right now. I've applied to so many internships and jobs, but I keep getting rejected. I feel like I'm just not good enough.
